cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with infinite games and their winning strategies, which are often studied in the context of logic and automata theory. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a likely category as the paper specifically deals with two-player games and their objectives. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper presents algorithms for solving energy parity games and their relation to other types of games. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with the synthesis of specifications, which is a common problem in AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the design and synthesis of specifications, which can be seen as a programming language problem.
